{
  "stem": "12674.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What, what, what they were there for was they got-- they got the number, and they had to give them-- they got a number, and they were told to give them 1,000 names for next Thursday.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's what they had to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had a list of everybody, that's what they were there for, to win out who was going to go on the next transport, and things like that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the head of the Jewish council at that time-- there had been others before, one of them was called-- it was a Czech man.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they wanted something from him that he would not give them, or they wanted him to make-- I do-- I honestly do not remember.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I used to know it once, but I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I've forgotten it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they put him on an iron bed, the Nazis, put him on an iron bedstead, and they poured gasoline over him and they set him on fire.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Epstein, his name was, or, or Echst-- I don't-- anyway, whatever.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this-- he was one of the-- so you could be a hero, even if you were doing work like that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, you didn't-- it wasn't required of you, but you didn't have to be.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Mr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Murmelstein, who was a rabbi from-- as it happened, it's a small world-- from, from Vienna, where I had grown up.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I knew him-- I knew him-- I knew him quite well, because I also know him aside from in his official function as a rabbi at the youth services in the temple.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My-- the parents of one of my girlfriends had a Jewish kosher restaurant.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he would come every Saturday afternoon to eat fish and challah, you know, jellied carp and things.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I knew him from there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
